An additional 124 cases of Covid-19 were reported on Sunday evening, as the SA total climbed to 3,158. Two additional deaths were reported, meaning that 54 people have now died in SA from the respiratory illness caused by the coronavirus. The total number of tests conducted to date is 114,711 — an increase of about 6,700 from the 108,021 reported on Saturday. In a statement on Sunday, health minister Dr Zweli Mkhize said that Gauteng was still the country's epicentre, with KwaZulu-Natal having had the most deaths, followed by the Western Cape. The provincial breakdown was provided as: There were 42 unallocated cases. 